SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A DRAFT OF THE FORM 990 IS PROVIDED TO THE ORGANIZATION BEFORE THE TAX RETURN IS FINALIZED. THE CEO AND FINANCE DIRECTOR REVIEW THE FORM AND APPLICABLE SCHEDULES TO ENSURE ACCURATE REPORTING OF DATA. ANY CHANGES, IF NECESSARY, ARE MADE AND THE FINAL RETURN IS FILED WITH THE APPROPRIATE TAXING AUTHORITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IS GIVEN TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ON AN ANNUAL BASIS TO READ AND SIGN. OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, AND KEY EMPLOYEES ARE REQUESTED TO DISCLOSE ANNUALLY ANY INTERESTS THAT COULD GIVE RISE TO CONFLICTS. THE ORGANIZATION ENFORCES COMPLIANCE IF AN INTEREST IS BROUGHT FORWARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: HUMAN RESOURCE PERSONNEL GATHER INFORMATION ON SALARY RATES IN THE AREA FOR DENTISTS AND CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICERS IN SIMILAR CLINICS. KEY EMPLOYEES AND THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER ARE COMPENSATED ACCORDINGLY. THE COMPENSATION AMOUNT IS SUBJECT TO APPROVAL BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL OF THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, AND PUBLIC DISCLOSURE COPIES OF FORM 990 ARE AVAILABLE AT THE MAIN OFFICE OF THE ORGANIZATION AT 190 PARK AVE, PORTLAND, ME 04102. COPIES ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.
